<p>Noting that per the new Draft Forum policy: <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-10629348/new-draft-forum-policies">http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-10629348/new-draft-forum-policies</a></p>
<p>Before they can ask for forum feedback on a draft, first-time authors will need to get their concepts &quot;greenlighted&quot;, either in the forums or IRC chatrooms, by two experienced reviewers from these lists:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/butterfly-squad-roster">Butterfly Squad Roster</a></li>
<li><a href="/authors-pages">Authors' Pages</a> (or someone who meets the requirements for an author page)</li>
<li><a href="/reviewers-spotlight-archive">Reviewers' Spotlight Archive</a></li>
<li><a href="/meet-the-staff">Meet The Staff</a></li>
</ul>
<p>Put simply, a reviewer has &quot;greenlighted&quot; a concept if they state straightforwardly (or when prompted) that they believe a draft of the premise would be successful on the mainsite, and/or that they think the author should progress to the drafting stage.</p>

