<p>Typically joining the team is invitation-only, but we are always welcome to people requesting to be considered for a team position.</p>
<p>The best way to be noticed is to provide high-quality critique at a relatively consistent activity rate. Butterfly Squad members are expected to be both good reviewers and active reviewers.</p>
<p>ETA: updating with some information, as it was brought to my attention that this comment is somewhat out of date.</p>
<p>Staff will occasionally reach out to consistently active quality reviewers to extend invitations to have their name put on the Roster. Staff will also happily take requests for consideration to join the team, whenever a reviewer wishes to put their name forth as someone whom authors can contact to seek feedback from. Any further questions or clarifications about this can be directed to me (Zyn) via wikidot PM.</p>

