<blockquote>
<p>Does a reviewer need to be a successful author? Or can anyone provide critique assuming they are well written and constructive with their criticism?</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Yes, anyone can provide critique as long as they give constructive criticism (save for people given a cease and desist due to previous problematic critiques). The ability to greenlight however has more standards.</p>
<p>I would suggest however that you take some time to read how other people critique before doing it yourself (The <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/butterfly-squad-roster">butterfly squad roster</a> is a great place to start. It hosts many experienced members of the forum). Many people need examples of constructive criticism to understand what makes it good.</p>

