<p>Not at all! The chef/food metaphor applies here: while chefs are more likely to give good advice on how to improve food, one doesn't necessarily need to be a chef to comment on whether food tastes good and what can be done to improve a dish (to their taste, at least).</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Despite not being a successful author, I wish to be a reviewer.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Excellent! We could always use more talented reviewers on the site.</p>
<p>We do have a number of critique resources available in the <a href="/guide-hub">Guide Hub</a>, so feel free to reference the writing guides as you get started writing reviews in the forums.</p>

