			<div class="content" id="post-content-4491022">
									

<blockquote>
<p>So, what if your feedback was vague and unhelpful, yet you could still use some review on an idea. As, you can’t post multiple threads for one idea meaning the SCP really only has one shot in the idea section.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Presuming that you mean that the <em>feedback you received</em> was vague, and not the feedback you yourself gave was vague, you can and should reach out to reviewers.</p>
<p>If you're having trouble getting further replies on a thread, you can go to the <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/chat-guide">IRC chatroom</a> and ask people there if they can reply to the forum thread, or message a <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/contact-staff">staff member</a> and ask them if they can direct chat attention to the thread. You can also reach out to a reviewer on the <a href="/butterfly-squad-roster">Butterfly Squad Roster</a>.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Also, does someone have to request a sandbox draft or can you add a link to one in your idea critique out of your own choice?</p>
</blockquote>
<p>If you want to preemptively link a sandbox draft, it has to be optional reading only. Reviewers should not need to read a full draft to understand and discuss the core concept of a piece. An author should be prepared to answer reviewer questions directly, rather than needing to default to asking a reviewer to dig through a full draft for the answers.</p>

							</div>

								
					
