<blockquote>
<p>is it still alright to leave unsolicited crit on threads we find interesting,</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Totally alright! Encouraged, even. The best case scenario we're aiming for is reviewers enjoying the critique process by finding material that they are enthusiastic about critiquing.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>is the idea to ensure that prospective authors are taking the initiative to find someone on their own?</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Sort of. The main concern to address was that a lot of feedback simply went effectively ignored, as authors either did not respond to reviewers entirely or immediately dropped a concept after receiving a review that noted changes needed to be made.</p>
<p>By asking authors to take the initiative to reach out, the intention is to establish that the author is a. active and likely to reply to a reviewer and b. willing and able to put in more than just the bare minimum effort to get a concept review.</p>

